The paper deals with the problem of distributing a real-time video sequence to a group of wireless devices using network coding. This involves issues related to information theory (cs.IT) such as coding conflicts and transmission conflicts, as well as networking (cs.NI) issues related to cooperative wireless devices. The paper also considers the characteristics of the video sequence, such as its importance and hard deadline, which are relevant to multimedia (cs.MM) and systems (cs.SY) research. Finally, the paper evaluates the performance of the proposed algorithms using simulation results over a real video sequence, which is relevant to computer vision (cs.CV) research.
